of which were then converted they licensed the name from roy rogers and operated the restaurants from  through  the first location opened in  in the baileys crossroads section of falls church virginia on the corner of leesburg pike and carlin springs road  leesburg pike not far from the hot shoppes on columbia pike that roy rogers is now a mcdonalds another jr hot shoppes that became a roy rogers was at  river road in bethesda maryland directly across the street from the original headquarters of marriott corporation marriott senior executives and members of the marriott family were frequent patrons of the location the site is also now a mcdonalds in  marriott corporation bought the ginos restaurant chain for  million the company converted  of the  restaurants to roy rogers to expand in the baltimorewashington area in  marriott sold the chain for  million to hardees a southern chain seeking to expand into the midatlantic market again hardees converted the remaining nonfranchised locations into hardees restaurants many of the new hardees continued to feature roy rogers fried chicken the conversion of the roy rogers chain ended in a customer revolt so serious that they actually aborted the idea and returned the roy rogers brand to stores initially converted the restaurants promoted new flamebroiled hamburgers but they were not the same as the original roy rogers products and they later failed hardees finally sold the remaining roy rogers locations to mcdonalds wendys and boston market between  and  this left  roy rogers franchisees with two dozen freestanding locations in addition to locations owned by hmshost in travel plazas along highways in the northeast filming for the first television commercials advertising roy rogers restaurants took place in the apple valley california area where rogers lived with his family in  and  rogers and friends earl bascom and mel marion were filmed at various locations including the historic las flores ranch in summit valley and the campbell ranch in victorville new ownership relaunchedit roy rogers restaurant in westminster maryland in a former ginos building owned by the plamondon companies remodeled in  roy rogers restaurant in germantown maryland owned by the plamondon companies opened in  plamondon companies took the lead among franchisees in developing products hosting training sessions and shooting new food photography for their stores plamondon companies is run by jim plamondon and peter plamondon jr the two sons of peter plamondon sr head of the restaurant division at marriott when the roy rogers brand was created roy rogers was relaunched as roy rogers franchise company llc in  when plamondon companies bought the trademark and franchise system from imasco the former owner of hardees in  cke restaurants acquired hardees from imasco but imasco held on to the roy rogers trademark and franchise system plamondon negotiated with imasco for three years before a private purchase agreement was reached in  the first new roy rogers restaurant after many years of decline was opened in frederick maryland by plamondon in  based in frederick maryland the plamondon companies is a privately held company with annual revenues of  million in  the plamondon companies opened its doors with their first roy rogers restaurant as of  the plamondon companies own and operate  roy rogers restaurants and oversee  franchise locations in the midatlantic region the company is seeking franchisees to continue roy rogers expansion throughout the midatlantic region key datesedit this article is in a list format that may be better presented using prose you can help by converting this article to prose if appropriate editing help is available august   the first roy rogers opens at  leesburg pike falls church virginia s roy rogers chain flourishes under marriott several hundred franchised and company units open s first long island stores open in greenvale nassau county new york and commack suffolk county new york  stores in uniondale island trees and farmingdale all nassau county new york open  long island store opens in shirley new york in suffolk county  roy rogers in fairfax virginia on little river turnpike at the border of alexandria virginia is robbed in a highprofile case where five employees were herded into the restaurants freezer and shot in the head four people were killed and one survived s franchisee plamondon enterprises inc opens seven and acquires three roy rogers locations  marriott purchases the ginos restaurant chain for  million and converts many of the restaurants to roy rogers  marriott threatens to take the riese family a franchisee to court when they discovered the rieses were reserving space for häagen dazs and godfathers pizza in a property slotted for a times square roy rogers restaurant  marriott decides to get out of the fastfood business and sell its roy rogers howard johnsons bobs big boy and other chains to concentrate on its fastfood operations catering to captive buyers at airports and along turnpikes  a total of  roy rogers locations are in operation—primarily in the northeast and midatlantic states  marriott sells roy rogers to hardees subsidiary of imasco for  million in its plan to exit the fastfood business  hardees converts  roy rogers locations to hardees  due to customer loyalty hardees reconverts  former roy rogers locations back to roy rogers  jordan mcgrath case  taylor inc a new york advertising agency is hired to promote the roy rogers brand  ronald r powell who ran roy rogers from  to  under marriott becomes president of roy rogers and is believed to have influenced hardees decision in dropping its conversion strategy and restoring the chain to its original identity  with much fanfare and a celebrating featuring cowboys and pony rides for children an experimental super roy rogers opens at the vienna virginia location the store features usual roy rogers food items but with added flair such as third pound burgers bbq sauce served with a ladle and an improved dining room with television screens  hardees sells  companyowned roy rogers restaurants in the philadelphia region to boston market for  million  hardees sells  companyowned roy rogers restaurants in the new york region to wendys international inc  hardees sells  companyowned roy rogers restaurants in the baltimorewashington region to mcdonalds for  million  only  roy rogers franchisees remain operating a total of about  units through the northeast including  units in highway travel plazas and  in new york city  cke restaurants carls jr acquires hardees from imasco imasco retains roy rogers trademark due to a franchisee lawsuit  the riese family now franchisees of  roy rogers restaurants sues cke restaurants and imasco for  million claiming the roy rogers chain has been destroyed through a series of marketing errors of epic proportions  cke enters into a management agreement for the six roy rogers restaurants currently operated by hardees cke also agrees to perform services relating to the continued franchise operations of the roy rogers restaurant chain for  million over three years s franchisee plamondon enterprises inc opens two and acquires three roy rogers locations  plamondon enterprises inc opens a new roy rogers prototype unit in frederick maryland  plamondon enterprises inc develops and opens a new roy rogers unit in germantown maryland sugarloaf shopping center in a former burger king  imasco sells roy rogers trademark rights to plamondon enterprises inc roy rogers franchise co  hmshost formerly host marriott services signs agreement to continue operating roy rogers in travel plazas  roy rogers franchise company unveils its roy rogers rides again refranchising growth initiative  roy rogers restaurants launches royrogersrestaurantscom website  roy rogers opens in gaithersburg maryland in a former hardees  todd restaurants inc sign new longterm pioneer franchise agreement for its four roy rogers locations in alexandria virginia  smithgiffor