logy devices and systems throughout our history rogers has successfully evolved and adapted our products technologies and manufacturing presence to meet the demands of current and emerging markets we have expanded globally and built strong relationships with our customers worldwide as a result we have led the way in our chosen industries with new materials and solutions that empower our customers to invent the future the new york stock exchange rogers corporation celebrates fifteen years of trading on the nyse by ringing the closing bell key milestones on our journey  founded by peter rogers as a paper manufacturer  expanded into nonpaper products with fiberloy® phenolic resin plastics  introduced rtduroid® electronics insulation  introduced poron® product line and expanded into europe  listed on american stock exchange  lurie research  development center opens  formed durel® joint venture with m  acquired bisco® silicones  opened facility in china and acquired full interest in durel  celebrated th anniversary  acquired portions of mti global silicone  acquired esorba® urethanes and sk utis  acquired curamik electronics gmbh  acquired arlon circuit materials and engineered silicones  acquired dewal precision ptfe  uhmw film  tape products  acquired diversified silicone products inc  moved corporate headquarters to chandler arizona usa today rogers is the technology leader in our chosen markets we imagine what could be possible then apply our creativity research and development expertise to create new products and services for our customers complete history for more information about the complete history of rogers please view the pdf document below rogers history pdf previous presidents bruce d hoechner   present robert wachob  walter boomer  harry birkenruth  norman greenman  saul silverstein  charles ray  knight rogers  henry rogers  peter rogers  our company global locations contact us investor relations rogers news careers asia belgium germany united states websi